The Chief of Staff to President Buhari, Prof, Ibrahim Agboola Gambari has said there can be no development without peace. He made the assertion during a lecture he delivered as part of activities marking the 30th anniversary and 14 convocation ceremony of Delta State University, Abraka. Prof. Gambari said there could be no durable development without peace.” Prof. Gambari noted that “Development, Peace, Respect for Human Rights and free elections are attributes of any developing nation.” He siad, “You can have peace by the building on inclusiveness.
What Africa needs is a strong leader and strong institutions where youths are trained.” Prof. Gambari urged Nigerians to invest in Nigeria with a view to developing the economy of the nation. On insecurity, he said the Islamic Sect, Boko Haram is in 17 Local Governments in the Northern parts of Nigeria, stressing that overcoming the security challenges in Nigeria, is the business of the whole nation. “Security should be everybody’s business.” “Education itself is not a guarantee of success, therefore you need to embrace the mindset of continuous learning and reading.” Pro-Chancellor of Delta State University, Prof. Sam Oyovbaire commended Prof. Gambari for honouring the invitation of the institution, especially in the celebration of its 30th anniversary and 14th convocation ceremony.